  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Starting at 5th level, you can interfere with the flow of ki in an opponent's body. When you hit another creature with a melee weapon attack, you can spend 1 use of this feature to attempt a stunning strike. The target must succeed on a Constitution saving throw or be stunned until the end of your next turn.</p><p>You can do this a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus and regain any expended uses at the end of a long rest. At any point when you are out of uses of this feature, you can expend 1 ki instead.</p>",
